The audio for the most part was good except for approximately 61 minutes in where it goes out of sync for around 5 minutes or so, then it rights itself.

The video quality was good for a cam. There were a few times where the chap filming moves the cam-corder also a number of times that people move around the cinema (y would u move around during the movie??) but all in all very watch-able.

As for the movie....i seriously think it's time to let this doggy die. To me it was all over the place. The director Paul W.S. Anderson is like Michael Bay but without the class or refinement. He likes fast paced action but doesn't always hit the mark which leaves the viewer thing "what just happened"? Also, his movies go for just over 70 minutes which i guess says alot. 

Anyway, these are just my thoughts. Hope someone finds them useful.
